<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-10-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-10-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="333" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d333">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 300.115/28386</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Commercial Adviser of the British Embassy</hi>
                                    (<persName corresp="#p_CSRF1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Crawford</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Foreign
                                    Trade Adviser of the Department of State</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FWB1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Fleming</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-10-29">
                                        <hi rend="italic">October 29, 1915</hi>.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr.</hi>
                                <persName corresp="#p_FWB1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Fleming</hi></persName>: In reply to your
                                letter of the 23d instant, I am to acquaint you that it would be
                                impracticable to extend the date for the submission of cases beyond
                                November 1.</p>
                            <p>I understand, however, that you may not be able to present complete
                                by that date the cases filed in your office and I am authorized to
                                say that in the circumstances preliminary applications for all these
                                cases should be made by November 1, and where required the
                                additional details may be furnished later.</p>
                            <p>Yours very truly,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_CSRF1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">R. F. Crawford</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>